content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1262.30 - Fueling prohibited while engine running or being heated

State Regulations

Aircraft fueling is prohibited while the engine of
the aircraft being fueled is running or is being heated. Fuel shall be
delivered or drained through hose and connections listed by Underwriters'
Laboratories, Inc. Notes
